  "prompt": "What are some movies, songs or books in which the characters have a non monogamous relationship (like polyamorous or a trouple)?",
  "response": "There are several movies, songs, and books that explore non-monogamous relationships, including polyamory and triads. Here are some notable examples:\n\n### Movies:\n1. **\"Professor Marston and the Wonder Women\" (2017)** - This film tells the true story of psychologist William Moulton Marston, who created Wonder Woman, and his polyamorous relationship with his wife Elizabeth and their partner Olive Byrne.\n2. **\"Savages\" (2012)** - This crime thriller features a love triangle between two drug dealers and a woman who is in a relationship with both of them.\n3. **\"Henry & June\" (1990)** - Based on the real-life relationship between writer Henry Miller, his wife June, and Ana\u00efs Nin, this film explores their complex and non-monogamous relationship.\n4. **\"The Dreamers\" (2003)** - Directed by Bernardo Bertolucci, this film features a complex and intimate relationship between three characters that blurs the lines of traditional monogamy.\n5. **\"Design for Living\" (1933)** - This classic film, directed by Ernst Lubitsch, follows a woman who falls in love with two men and they all agree to live together without jealousy.\n\n### Songs:\n1. **\"Polyamorous\" by Breaking Benjamin** - This song explores themes of multiple romantic connections.\n2. **\"Candyland\" by Aqua** - While not explicitly about polyamory, the song's lyrics and music video suggest a playful and non-traditional approach to relationships.\n3. **\"Polyamorous Love Song\" by The Generals** - This song explicitly celebrates polyamorous relationships.\n\n### Books:\n1. **\"The Ethical Slut\" by Dossie Easton and Janet W. Hardy** - A seminal book on polyamory and non-monogamy, offering guidance and personal stories.\n2. **\"More Than Two: A Practical Guide to Ethical Polyamory\" by Franklin Veaux and Eve Rickert** - This book provides practical advice and insights into polyamorous relationships.\n3. **\"The Commitments\" by Roddy Doyle** - While primarily about a soul band in Dublin, the book also explores complex, non-monogamous relationships among the characters.\n4. **\"The Seven Husbands of Evelyn Hugo\" by Taylor Jenkins Reid** - This novel delves into the life of a fictional Hollywood star, revealing her non-monogamous relationships and complex love life.\n\nThese works provide a range of perspectives on non-monogamous relationships, from celebratory to complex and challenging.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
